result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt:
9:35 a.m. Defendant Eduardo L Corral in court with attorney Gary J. Kryshak. Louis John Molepske appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Victim D.J. is present as well. Cases 15CF164, 16CT78, 15CF171, 16CF20.
Amended Information is filed in 15CF164 amending Ct 1 and adding counts 2 & 3. Reading is wavied.
Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
 W/H Sentence: 24 mo Probation w/conditions.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
15CF164 Count 1: No Contest
15CF164 Count 2: No Contest
15CF164 Count 3: No Contest
16CT78: No Contest

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty 15CF164 cts 1, 2, & 3 and 16CT78.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.
 
16CF20 and 15CF171 are dismissed and read in.
Victim makes statements to the Court.
Exhibits P#1, P#2, & P#3 photos of victim injuries.

DA Molepske makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Kryshak concurs with joint agreement. 
Informs the Court of 1 days jail credit.
Defendant makes apologetic statements in Court.

BY THE COURT:****PROBATION****
15CF164 Count 1: I/S Sentence: 270 days jail - stayed 24 months  Probation
Conditions:
150 days jail - half in jail and other half on EM if found eligible w/huber. 60 days to start jail sentence and go today to get start date. 1 day credit.
  AODA & comply with treatment recommendations.
  Maintain absolute sobriety with regards to alcohol and illegal drugs.
  Do not possess or consume alcohol or be on premises where alcohol is served/sold as its primary business except within scope of your employment.
  Must sign release form for all treatment providers.  Sign all releases of information for all doctors and other treatment providers and pharmacy.
$629 Restitution  Victim D. J.
  Obtain and maintain full-time employment.  
Engage and comply in any other counseling including Anger Managment as recommended by the Agent.
Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge on each counts.
Apology letter to be given to Agent first.
No contact with victim, except for apology letter.
Pay costs.

15CF164 Count 2: I/S Sentence: 270 days jail, concurrent - stayed 24 months  Probation, concurrent. Pay costs & DNA surcharge. Comply with same conditions Ct 1.
15CF164 Count 3: I/S Sentence: 45 days jail, concurrent  - stayed 24 months  Probation, concurrent. Pay costs & DNA surcharge. Comply with same conditions Ct 1.
16CT78: $150 fine + costs + DNA surcharge.

Appeal rights provided.
